I don't get the point behind making a 700 mb BRRip of a movie that is this long. I thought the whole idea behind converting a movie down to around 700 MB was to be able to fit it on one CD-R, which is not possible cause of the run time. 

Not complaining though, makes for a speedy download when you're on the go.

@guerrillapirate: you are correct that the point of encoding something at (or just under) 700MB is to fit on a CD. But this is somewhat *over* at 748MB, though it could have been 700MB if the ripper knew what he was doing. In any event, the smaller the file, the faster the download. 700MB is usually a good all-around compromise, but this is an unusually long movie.
